Jackson Byrnes, 18, has flown from Lismore in New South Wales to be operated on by renowned neurosurgeon Dr Charlie Teo .
The 18-year-old was told he had a stage four brain tumour that was too deep and aggressive to be safely operated on .
His family and friends have been desperately trying to raise $80,000 needed to pay for the operation .
Dr Teo said he was willing to perform the risky surgery if the family understood the risks .